The paper proposes a method for sequence labeling using sum-product networks (SPNs) and higher-order linear-chain conditional random fields (HO-LC-CRFs). This work involves machine learning and natural language processing, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on deep models and their effectiveness for sequence labeling. The second likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as optical character recognition and phone classification. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper proposes a novel approach for modeling complex relations in sequence data. The fourth likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper applies the proposed method to optical character recognition. The fifth likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper mentions the use of SPNs for secure multi-party computation.
